body:
@domdom82 thanks for volunteering  

> I suggest making a build on our Jenkins that does a vagrant up and checks the output.

I would prefer to see something externally test this, but I guess for now we will use an internal server, but even with that I will suggest to have all the scripts in open (i.e. `tools/travis/test-vagrant.sh`)

I recommend that we mark deprecated whisk.async() and whisk.done() once we get this in.
We can also discuss the ability to support callback as a parameter in addition of supporting Promises like: 

```
function main(params, context, callback) { 
... }
```

This is concern that I have, but I don't know if its part of this issue or it can be handle in a different issue.

I would like to have the ability to use export and not forced to have a global `main` function.

we can design what should be exported I'm open to brainstorm on alternatives like convention
export.main = function () {..} or export.handler = function () {..}
export = function() { ..}

the benefit is that it's easier to use things like webpack, and other bundlers, and also for using require when it comes to unit testing.
